1. DNS resolution check (is it DNS-level blocking?)
nslookup claude.ai
nslookup api.anthropic.com
nslookup console.anthropic.com
nslookup platform.claude.com
2. Actual HTTPS connectivity (is it IP/SNI-level blocking?)
curl -I https://claude.ai
curl -I https://api.anthropic.com
curl -I https://console.anthropic.com
curl -I https://registry.npmjs.org
3. Raw TCP port check (bypasses HTTP layer, tells you if port 443 itself is reachable)
powershell -Command "Test-NetConnection claude.ai -Port 443"
powershell -Command "Test-NetConnection api.anthropic.com -Port 443"
4. Trace where it's failing (timeout vs explicit reset vs redirect to a block page)
tracert api.anthropic.com
tracert claude.ai
